         <abstract>
            <p>The Securities and Exchange Commission has proposed requiring corporations to disclose the current replacement cost of both inventory and plant. The Financial Accounting Standards Board, on the other hand, requires disclosure of adjustments to the historical cost of such assets for changes in the value of the monetary unit since their purchase. The two kinds of disclosure are not necessarily mutually exclusive, and both are required to compute the best measure of income.</p>
          </abstract>
